[_Blog for a Cause!_](https://advox.globalvoices.org/wp-
content/downloads/gv_blog_advocacy2.pdf), the [Global Voices Guide of Blog
Advocacy](https://advocacy.globalvoicesonline.org/2008/01/30/blog-for-a-cause-
the-global-voices-guide-of-blog-advocacy/), is now [available in
Spanish](https://advox.globalvoices.org/wp-
content/downloads/\(spanish\)gv_blog_advocacy.pdf) thanks to this translation
by [María Florencia Puente](http://la-misionera.blogspot.com/) from[ Global
voices en Español](https://es.globalvoicesonline.org/).

The guide outlines easy-to-follow tips on how to use blogs as part of
campaigns against injustice and features successful examples of advocacy blogs
from around the world. It is divided into five sections:

  1. Frequently asked questions about what blog advocacy is
  2. The 5 key elements of any successful advocacy blog
  3. The 4 steps to creating an advocacy blog
  4. How to make your blog a vibrant community of active volunteers 
  5. Tips to help blog activists stay safe online.

_[Blog Por Una Causa!](https://advox.globalvoices.org/wp-
content/downloads/\(spanish\)gv_blog_advocacy.pdf)_ is availble for download
as a PDF file. You may need to install the free [Adobe Acrobat
Reader](http://www.adobe.com/products/acrobat/readstep2.html) to view it.

Please download _[Blog Por Una Causa!](https://advox.globalvoices.org/wp-
content/downloads/\(spanish\)gv_blog_advocacy.pdf)_ and help us translating
the guide in your language.

